  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multi sectoral assistance to Congolese Refugees and Asylum seekers in Nchelenge District (Luapula Province of Zambia)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving assistance in multi-sectors (Protection, Food, Shelter, Health, Nutrition) to Congolese refugees/asylum seekers. With this CERF grant, UNHCR will provide shelter kits to 10,000 refugees, tents to 625 vulnerable families, and sanitary materials to 6,800 women. The project will benefit a total of 20,000 people and will last six months.</narrative>
  </description>
